{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This quick start guide uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Although not strictly required, it simplifies many aspects of cross-platform distribution and provides a platform-agnostic configuration format for specifying things such as app icons and custom URL schemes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re new to Swift, we recommend starting with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Installing Swift Bundler","type":"heading","anchor":"Installing-Swift-Bundler"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Follow ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler?tab=readme-ov-file#installation-","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"code":"mint","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the preferred installation method on macOS and Linux as of the last update to this quick start guide.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Installing system dependencies","type":"heading","anchor":"Installing-system-dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each backend has different requirements. In this guide we’ll use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" which uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on macOS, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on Linux, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on Windows, and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS\/tvOS. Click through the backend relevant to your machine for detailed installation requirements. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" have no system dependencies."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Using Swift Bundler’s SwiftCrossUI template","type":"heading","anchor":"Using-Swift-Bundlers-SwiftCrossUI-template"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift Bundler provides many built-in templates; we’ll use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftCrossUI"},{"type":"text","text":" template. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftCrossUI"},{"type":"text","text":" template uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" to select the most appropriate backend at compile time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["swift bundler create HelloWorld --template SwiftCrossUI","cd HelloWorld"]},{"level":2,"text":"Running your app","type":"heading","anchor":"Running-your-app"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Running your new app with Swift Bundler is as simple as it gets!"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["swift bundler run"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On macOS you can provide the ","type":"text"},{"code":"--device <device_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option to run the app on a connected iOS or tvOS device, or the ","type":"text"},{"code":"--simulator <simulator_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option to run the app in a simulator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["# You can use any substring of the target device name. For example,","# \"iPhone\" matches any device connected with \"iPhone\" in its name.","swift bundler run --device \"iPhone\"","swift bundler run --simulator \"iPhone 15\""]},{"level":2,"text":"Making a change","type":"heading","anchor":"Making-a-change"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sources\/HelloWorld\/HelloWorldApp.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" in an editor of your choosing. Change "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Hello, World!\""},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Hello, Earth!\""},{"type":"text","text":". Repeat the previous step to verify that your changes get reflected."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"All done","type":"heading","anchor":"All-done"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’re good to go! If you make something cool with SwiftCrossUI let us know so we can add your project to our showcase once the SwiftCrossUI website is up and running!"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/quick-start"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating a cross-platform SwiftCrossUI app with Swift Bundler."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI"]]},"kind":"article","sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"title":"Quick start","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Getting Started","generated":true,"anchor":"Getting-Started","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-virtual-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/Swif